def_en: Speakers and writers use one's to indicate that something belongs or relates to people in general, or to themselves in particular.

def_cn: （one is 或尤当 has 为助动词时 one has 的一种口语形式）
def_en: One's can be used as a spoken form of 'one is' or 'one has', especially when 'has' is an auxiliary verb.  →see: one;
